label.value: paraffin embedding and Fixation quality check report

definition.value: required quality check list for the procedure of paraffin embedding and/or fixation.
a specimen which represent remaining portion of a specimen obtained for clinical purposes that is no longer needed for its original purpose and that would otherwise be discarded
A specimen that derives from an organism and might contain infectious materials.
A training manual is a book or booklet of instructions, designed to improve the quality of a performed task.

A data item infromation content entity that represent any data that could potentially identify a specific individual. Any information that can be used to distinguish one person from another and can be used for de-anonymizing anonymous data can be considered PII.
A sequencing assay which involves the determination of the arrangement of the amino acid sequence of a protein.
A database which represent libraries of life sciences information, collected from scientific experiments, published literature, high-throughput experiment technology, and computational analysis.
A bioinformatics analysis data transformation which two or more things are positioned in a straight line or parallel to each other

A bioinformatics analysis that produces data structure that improves the speed of data retrieval operations on a database table at the cost of additional writes and storage space to maintain the index data structure
A bioinformatics analysis which referes to the process of compressing to reduze the size of genome file
A measured expression level which refers to the characteristic of preferentially expressing a parental allele in the hybrid due to variations in regulatory sequences from the parental genomes.
A measured expression level measurement datum which represent copy number variation (CNV) obtained by microarray

A measured expression level measurement datum which refers to represent small non-coding RNAs of 19-24 nucleotides in length that downregulate gene expression during various crucial cell processes such as apoptosis, differentiation and development.
A measured expression level which refers to activity (the expression) of thousands of genes at once, to create a global picture of cellular function.
A mesurement datum that represent all of the protein-coding regions of genes in a genome (known as the exome)

label.value: single molecule real time sequencing data

definition.value: A single molecule real time sequencing data is DNA sequence data generated from parallelized single molecule DNA sequencing method.
A DNA sequence data which represent the the complete DNA sequence of an organism's genome at a single time
DNA sequence data which represent genomic DNA obtained from environmental samples
RNA sequence data which represent the complete complement of transcripts in a sample, at a given time
RNA sequence data which is about the 16s gene of one or more organisms.
A genetic variation analysis which involves identifying biologically interesting variants by prioritizing individual variants, for example, homozygous variants absent in control genomes.
An assay which attempt to select highly confident variants and remove the ones that are falsely called
A sequence alignment which align every residue in every sequence
A sequence alignment which align dissimilar sequences that are suspected to contain regions of similarity or similar sequence motifs within their larger sequence context
A multiple sequence alignment (MSA) is a sequence alignment of three or more biological sequences, generally protein, DNA, or RNA.

A sequence alignment bioinformatics analysis which identify regions of similarity that may indicate functional, structural and/or evolutionary relationships between two biological sequences (protein or nucleic acid)
A bioinformatics analysis which attempt to searching sequence databases by using alignment to a query sequence
A symbol that is used to specify options for command line programs.

Functional annotation is a bioinformatics analysis consists of attaching biological information to genomic elements such as: biochemical function, biological function, involved regulation and interactions and expression
A planned process which ensure data have undergone data cleansing to ensure they have data quality, that is, that they are both correct and useful.
A data validation process that checks that the data is in a specified format (template), e.g., dates have to be in the format DD/ MM/YYYY is correct
A data validating whech validate sequencing quality scores and measure the probability that a base is called incorrectly.
A processed material which contain a set of articles or equipment needed for a specific purpose.
A process material which contains DNA fragments that represent the entire genome of an organism.
An assay kit used for the technique of isolating DNA in a biological sample
A data item which represent datum related to reference genome used as a standard for comparison in basic research and clinical settings
A URL at which the data file file is stored.
A database is an information content entity that describe a structured set of data held in a computer, especially one that is accessible in various ways.
An assay kit processed material that include a set of articles or equipment needed for library construction
A report that represent the process of data collection and analysis through which the degree of conformity to predetermined standards and criteria are exemplified

label.value: sample derivative from specimen creation process

definition.value: A material processing that has as its input a specimen and as its output a sample derivative.
A data item that represent sort of archive that contains one or more files that have been reduced in size through file compression process
A bioinformatics analysis which analyse a genetic variation, for example to annotate its location, alleles, classification, and effects on individual transcripts predicted for a gene model.
An assay which represent the process of targeting detected known disease causing genetic variant for validation purposes
A validation of known variant assay which permits the direct detection of any point mutation in human DNA by analyzing the PCR products in an ethidium bromide-stained agarose or polyacrylamide gel
A molecular quality that represent the number of copies of a particular gene varies from one individual to the next (germline mutation)
A molecular quality that describe changes in copy number that have arisen in somatic tissues.

Secure file transfer is a planned process that represent data sharing via a secure, reliable delivery method. It is used to safeguard proprietary and personal data in transit and at rest. Most secure file sharing methods use standard protocols, including: Secure File Transfer Protocol (SFTP)
A data transfer protocol is a network protocol that provides file access, file transfer, and file management over any reliable data stream
A protocol plan specification which describes the process of data transfer between two entities
